cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

The paper is about an open-source toolkit for neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also emphasizes the efficiency, modularity, and extensibility of the toolkit, which are important topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as likely categories. Neural machine translation involves training neural networks, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category. Finally, the paper mentions source modalities, which could involve computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible category as well.
